review:
I have 1k hours in OW2, and didnt play OW1 as much as others on here. Here is a TLDR and then a full critique on this 'product'

The game is not good because the devs aren't good. If the content were as good as the game play the game would topple 95% of shooters out right now. The lies and greed are slowly burying this game.
//

General Stuff:
Should you play it? Only for free and strictly casual if fun is what you want.
Should you pay for DLC/Skins/etcetc? No, the prices of the INDIVIDUAL SKINS that were free are 20$ to 10$, the battlepasses and the recent one have a critical problem with select characters being chosen so you are cucked for 9weeks at a time if your character wasn't given the battlepass skin or even just a side pass one. The new 'PvE' is an 1hr30 minute campaign which I wouldn't say is worth 15$. 
Should you wait for changes/staff changes? Yes, the systems they have in place are destined to fail and the player base will drop drastically I can predict they will purge all of the head decision-makers and greed monsters.

//
//
//

Game Balance:
When you first play the game, you are going to be introduced to 3 roles, Tank being the worst, Support being the easiest and Damage being the most Impactful. The main rule to how this game has played for years now is the 'main role side role', which means there are main supports and side supports, main damage and side damage, and the most mind-boggling main tank side tank. (One of the tanks wasn't even a tank before this game came out)

Tank (DONT PLAY), Damage (PLAY), Support (FLIP A COIN).

Balance is something I couldn't care less about but the devs have completely ass-raped the ideas of balance in the last few patches. Leading to an Omega Buff to nerfing the character to them turning them into average over and over again. Which is questionable when characters like Kiriko have been hard meta for the last 6 seasons and now is being buffed???? But then they nerf Genji because of a passive that is no longer in the game. Its so strange, and its at this point not even the communities fault because no one even asks for some of these changes. Ill give you an example, so there is a character named Orisa and she is was tanky as hell and people complained that she survives for way too long and her ability to turn into an unkillable metal chunk was not fair and makes her unfun to fight. So the devs decided to buff her damage and her ultimate is now deadlier since it can go through shields. Then they remove her ability to shoot back, wait 9 weeks again and again and again and now 6 seasons later they fix the problem they called an unintended damage reduction multiplier that stacked and caused her to survive for too long. I dont understand why they wait to fix and change things that they didn't even want to keep and then go back on them with community backlash. But then do something random to just spice things up??? But all it does is kill the game.

IF ITS NOT BROKE DONT FIX IT PLEASE BLIZZARD

The killer of the balance of Overwatch 2 can be found in the Overbuff website. Without a doubt.

//
//
//

Game Repeatability (Prestige XP Borders Levels and Veteran Markers):

The most important and game-defining features was absolutely massacred on the start of OW2 and I realize the amount I missed out on with OW1. Player borders, which had a really cool and in depth feature. Which they scraped to kill all player originality. They have returned it but its not the same since its locked in the player profile and you wont be able to see other peoples if they have private profiles.

The only items you can earn with time spent is competitive currency which still only offers gold skin on your gun, after all the years of development they only have gold. Which is not hard to get. And on some characters it is not even able to be seen very well.

Veteran Players are only identified by old time-limited OW1 skins which are no longer earnable, which without a doubt will be resold for some profit through scarcity.

No prestige yet. lol.

